"form of   Maria .  When first introduced to England in the Middle Ages, it was Anglicized in pronunciation and respelled   Mary .  This French form was reintroduced into the English-speaking world as a separate name in the 19th century, and is still pronounced more or less in the French manner, although sometimes with the stress on the first syllable. It is now often used in combination with other names such as <i>Ellie</i>, <i>Chloe</i>, and <i>Lisa</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Dame Marie de Conty de Frémontiers was born about 1209, in Conty, Somme, Picardie, France, her father, Pierre II de CONTY, was 47 and her mother, Henriette de PICQUIGNY, was 31. She married Henri De Gournay Sur Aronde about 1225. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died after 1232, in Gournay-sur-Aronde, Oise, Picardie, France."},"et":{"environ 1209–après 1232":"umbes 1209–pärast 1232","1207–1261":"1207–1261","1209–1232":"1209–1232","1206–1257":"1206–1257","1232–1278":"1232–1278","1163–1231":"1163–1231","1179–1239":"1179–1239","1231":"1231","1197":"1197","1163":"1163","vers 1225":"umbes 1225","1261":"1261","1239":"1239","1206":"1206","1257":"1257","après 1232":"pärast 1232","1179":"1179","1278":"1278","1232":"1232","environ 1209":"umbes 1209","1209":"1209","1207":"1207","Gournay-sur-Aronde, Oise, Picardie, France":"Gournay-sur-Aronde, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Picquigny, Somme, Picardie, France":"Picquigny, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Conty, Somme, Picardie, France":"Conty, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"environ 1209–après 1232":"noin 1209–1232 jälkeen","1207–1261":"1207–1261","1209–1232":"1209–1232","1206–1257":"1206–1257","1232–1278":"1232–1278","1163–1231":"1163–1231","1179–1239":"1179–1239","1231":"1231","1197":"1197","1163":"1163","vers 1225":"noin 1225","1261":"1261","1239":"1239","1206":"1206","1257":"1257","après 1232":"1232 jälkeen","1179":"1179","1278":"1278","1232":"1232","environ 1209":"noin 1209","1209":"1209","1207":"1207","Gournay-sur